<Author>traveller2007
<Content>Well-priced, friendly hotel I booked a trip to Boston at 1 day's notice in early February, so needed to book a hotel quickly. I looked at some of the reviews on Trip Advisor and as the reviews were good, I booked via the central Radisson website. I got a 'Hot Deal' for the weekend nights I was staying but even the weekday rate that followed was excellent for what I got in return. The Boston airport shuttles all drop off right in front of the hotel door where the bellboy at the hotel was right there to help me. The reception staff were excellent - friendly, easy-going and well-informed about my reservation. I was whisked effortlessly up to my room and was thrilled with it! 23rd floor, amazing view and absolutely HUGE! It was more like a suite than a room (sitting area, two televisions, coffee facilities). The only down-side was the bathroom was very small and there was no bath - only a shower cubicle - but I didnt request a change as I loved the rest of the room so much! The room was incredibly clean and the domestic staff must be magicians - the bathroom was sparkling every day, as were all the hotel communal areas, even the pool (which wasnt great, I have to admit, but served its purpose and is fine for a centrally located city hotel and a brief swim). What made my stay even better was that the hotel was so well located to everything I wanted to see, so I was able to pop back during the day when it got too cold outside - although it was difficult to leave in the mornings as it was so comfortable! Also a nice little theatre on the ground floor, so always people around and area felt safe, even at weekends when offices were closed.I didnt actually eat breakfast in the hotel restaurant (breakfast wasnt included in the price and I dont eat first thing) but I found a great food court right across the road (with a great clam chowder) but the prices I saw seemed reasonable, even for room service. Coffee machine in room was a great additiona too! There isnt a subway stop nearby, but I used cabs which are cheap in Boston (compared to London!) I walked a lot of places anyway.My checkout was equally effortless and the staff were great about leaving luggage, ordering me a shuttle for the airport and my bill.I really oved it here - it's not a glamourous or plush hotel, the lobby isnt impressive and it hasn't got a history like other Boston hotels, but I was on a budget and wanted somewhere central and it ticked all the boxes... and more. I loved Boston and the hotel made my stay even better. Id recommend the Radisson to anyone and everyone, especially families given the size of the rooms (although beware of the high balconies if you have small kids). And I am still dreaming of that stunning view! 
