<Content>Great Hotel, Great Value, Great Location This was our first trip to Boston and we were a bit nervous about driving in the city as everything you read tells you not to drive in Boston. This hotel was not far off the highway and we booked the package that included parking and breakfast. We parked our car and didn't worry about it until we left the next day. We were told that we could leave the car in the garage up to 6 pm on check out day and had to bring the ticket to the hotel lobby to have it validated before we left. We ended up leaving our car parked there until 8pm and the ticket was validated without question and we didn't have to pay additional parking fees. The hotel is in an excellent location.We happend to be going to the Charles Play House to see the Blue Man Group (loved the show) and it was less than a 5 minute walk from the hotel. We walked to Quincy Market and the Prudential Center from the hotel and neither took more than 30 minutes. The Prudential was a bit closer than Quincy.... but the walk to Quincy was beautiful as you pass through the Boston Commons and so many beautiful buildings. The hotel room was very clean and the sleep number beds were comfortable. The bed linens are a very nice quality and they feel crisp and clean. We thought the room was a bit on the small side and the bathroom was small as well....but we didn't spend much time in the room, so it was fine. The concierge was very helpful and booked our tickets on the duck tour. I'm glad we paid the $2.50 fee to book ahead as you can only buy the tickets from the Prudential building the day of the tour. We saw signs early on in the afternoon saying the next available tour was for 6:30 that evening. We will most certainly return to the Radisson for future trips to Boston and would highly recommend it to all. 
